Key Match Events: Adil Rashid's 20 off 8 balls was crucial but not enough to win the match
Chris Woakes' 32 off 32 balls was a bright spot for England
Adam Zampa took 3-21, snaring Moeen Ali, Ben Stokes and Jos Buttler
Pre-Game Insights: England fancied themselves to have a real go and push whoever it was going to be all the way in the World Cup
Post-Match Reflections: England captain Jos Buttler: 'Disappointment. I feel like we are having the same chat after every game at the minute.'
Michael Vaughan: 'England have just got too many players out of form. They've lost their mojo - and when that happens you make poor decisions.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: England's very faint hopes of making the World Cup semi-finals are now officially over.
Five consecutive defeats for England, they've been bowled out each time.
They've lost six matches for the first time in a World Cup.
